Acting Commissioner Morgan of Customs and Border Protection (CBP) announced the official release of CBP's southwest border migration statistics for the month of August. He highlighted the Trump administration's efforts to address the crisis at the border, including historic agreements with Mexico and initiatives such as the Migrant Protection Protocols (MPP). He emphasized the role of Mexico in curbing illegal immigration and the need for them to do more. Commissioner Morgan also discussed the construction of the border wall and its effectiveness in securing the border. He expressed frustration with judicial activism that has hindered the administration's policies. He also addressed concerns about abuse in U.S. custody and the collection of DNA from individuals in CBP custody. Regarding the recent hurricane in the Bahamas, he stated that CBP is working to process individuals from the Bahamas in a humanitarian manner.